It stresses the importance of checking the presence of bats before the start of maintenance work inside buildings, since unintentional destruction of a single bed can kill up to 400 females and young people, likely destroying the entire local population.
Bats are protected and it's illegal to kill, torture or harass or destroy their shelters.
Elisabeth Ferrell, representative for the Scottish Bat Protection Association, encouraged the public to help.
